HEADWORD: mayhaw
<hw>mayhaw</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The hawthorn tree (<spn>Crataegus
aestivalis</spn>) of the Southern U. S. bearing a juicy acid scarlet
fruit often used in jellies or preserves.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> summer haw, <spn>Crataegus
aestivalis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
